objects.name: Pytha_theo
objects.string:
Pythagorean theorem

The Pythagorean theorem is a^2+b^2=c^2, where "a" and "b" are lengths of the legs of a right triangle and "c" is the length of the hypotenuse.

objects.name: Trigo_ratio
objects.string:
Trigonometric Ratios

The ratios of the sides of a right triangle are called trigonometric ratios. Three common trigonometric ratios are the sine (sin), cosine (cos), and tangent (tan).

objects.name: law_sines
objects.string:
Law of sines

The law of sines states that in any triangle, the ratio of the sine of an angle to the opposite side length is equal for all three angles and sides.
